'''Ikal Angelei''' is a Kenyan politician and environmentalist. She was born in [[Kitale]]. She was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 2012, in particular for her voicing of environmental implications of the [[Gilgel Gibe III Dam]], speaking on behalf of Kenyan indigenous communities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldmanprize.org/recipient/ikal-angelei |title=Ikal Angelei |publisher=[[Goldman Environmental Prize]]|accessdate=29 May 2012}}</ref>

