[[File:SolarGIS-Solar-map-Europe-en.png|thumb|right|Map of solar electricity potential in Europe]]
'''Solar power in Lithuania''' is a form of [[renewable energy in Lithuania]], and created 39 GWh of electricity in the first nine months of 2013.<ref>{{cite web |title= Ataskaitos apie elektros energiją, kurios gamybai naudojami atsinaujinantys energijos ištekliai |url= http://www.litgrid.eu/uploads/files/dir65/dir3/5_0.php |publisher= www.litgrid.eu |date= 2013-10-21 |accessdate= 2013-10-21 |language= Lithuanian }}{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

[[Lithuania]] has 1,580 small (from several kilowatts to 2,500&nbsp;kW) [[solar power]] plants with a total installed capacity of 59.4 MW which produce electricity for the country, and has an uncounted number of private power plants which make electricity only for their owners.<ref>{{cite web|title= Suvilioti dosnių išmokų puolė statyti saulės jėgaines |url= http://verslas.delfi.lt/archive/article.php?id=58848339 |publisher= delfi.lt |date=2012-06-04 |accessdate=2012-06-10 | language = Lithuanian }}</ref>

